fJhRAy0wP2owSz8RYlDKlEKaRTHSTbGJ0A9f6-2B3ACTkFuJhWX-2B6H8ozvX-2FAYg6I8UtIqo=
F68NYxP8DxvtPSj4X8kjVJJlTQ18tyvlA9AERWUZTl7LQwa0" style=3D"color: #8b9dc3" =
target=3D"_blank">that includes opioids</a>. Even though drug sales are aga=
inst Facebook=E2=80=99s terms =E2=80=94 not to mention illegal =E2=80=94 se=
veral representatives reported that drug dealers were slipping through the =
cracks. =E2=80=9CYour platform is still being used to circumvent the law, a=
nd allow people to buy highly addictive drugs without a prescription,=E2=80=
=9D said Rep. David McKinley, (R-WV). =E2=80=9CWith all due respect, Facebo=
ok is actually enabling an illegal activity and, in so doing, you are hurti=
